            <p>Quartiles are specific percentiles that divide data into four quarters. Q1 (first quartile) is the 25th percentile. Q2 is the 50th percentile, which is exactly the same as the median. Q3 is the 75th percentile. The interquartile range (IQR) is the difference between Q3 and Q1.</p>
          </div>
